-- Digiturk Gets $260 Million Four-Year Loan Via Standard Bank
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-06-14T11:00:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/digiturk-gets-260-million-four-year-loan-via-standard-bank.html
Digiturk, the Turkish digital
broadcaster controlled by Cukurova Holding AS, got a loan of
$260 million from banks led by  Standard Bank Group Ltd. (SBK) , the
loan’s arranger Standard Unlu Menkul Degerler AS said.  ING Groep NV (INGA) ,  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN) ,  Turkiye Is
Bankasi (ISATR)  AS participated in the lending, which has a four-year
maturity, the Istanbul-based broker said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Digiturk got rights last year to show the country’s top
soccer matches for an annual fee of $321 million.  Cukurova’s partner in Digiturk is Providence Equity
Partners Inc., a private equity firm based in Providence,  Rhode
Island  that holds 46 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 